The paper deals with optimization methods for training deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on image classification datasets, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The use of adaptive learning rates is also a common technique in optimization methods for deep learning, which further supports the likelihood of cs.LG and cs.NE as likely sub-categories.
